snippet: The National Transportation Safety Board said it had interviewed the pilots of a Southwest Airlines flight that landed at the wrong airport this week.
abstract: Federal investigators say pilots of Southwest Airlines flight that landed at wrong Branson, Mo, airport realized their mistake only after they were on runway, forcing them to brake heavily to bring plane to stop; no one was injured in incident, which involved Boeing 737-700 with 124 passengers and five crew members on board.
lead_paragraph: The National Transportation Safety Board said it had interviewed the pilots of a Southwest Airlines flight that landed at the wrong airport this week.

headline.main: More Details in Mistaken Landing of a Plane
